TY  - JOUR
AU  - Kadan, Ohad
AU  - Manela, Asaf
T1  - Liquidity and the strategic value of information
PY  - 2025
Y1  - 2025/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfae040
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 29
IS  - 1
SP  - 1
EP  - 32
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - In Kyle (1985), the ratio of fundamental variance to price impact measures the value of information to a monopolist strategic informed investor. We show that this same statistic provides an approximation for the value of information in a more general setting with multiple differentially informed investors, and estimate it using high-frequency stocks data. We find that the value of information rises during crises. The value of information is higher for large, growth, and momentum stocks. Its most dramatic spikes occur at the start of the Covid-19 pandemic and the financial crisis of 2008, when the Fed announces liquidity facilities.
Y2  - 4/24/2026
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfae040
ER  - 




